---
import PortalLayout from "../layouts/PortalLayout.astro";
---

<PortalLayout title="Onboarding" mainBg="#fdf2f8">
  <div class="max-w-4xl">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2">Welcome to Our Dev Family!</h1>
    <p class="text-stone-600 mb-8">Everything you need to get connected and building with us</p>

    <div class="space-y-8">

      <!-- Welcome / How It Works -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700 mb-4">How We Build</h2>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">At Spirit Media, you don&rsquo;t need a local dev environment. All code lives on our shared dev server called <strong>Bethel</strong>. You connect from your machine via SSH and use <strong>Claude Code</strong> &mdash; an AI assistant that reads the project&rsquo;s rules, knows the full stack, and does the heavy lifting for you.</p>

        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">The more you work within the system, the more Claude can help. It reads each site&rsquo;s configuration automatically &mdash; design system, SEO rules, CMS setup, deploy workflow &mdash; so you don&rsquo;t have to memorize anything. Just follow the setup below and you&rsquo;ll be building in minutes.</p>

        <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg">
          <p class="font-bold text-red-800 text-sm mb-2">Three things are required &mdash; skip one and you&rsquo;re stuck</p>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3 text-sm">
            <div class="bg-white border border-red-100 rounded-lg p-3 text-center">
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Tailscale VPN</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-1">Bethel is invisible without it &mdash; no VPN, no connection</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-red-100 rounded-lg p-3 text-center">
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">SSH Key</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-1">Password login is disabled &mdash; your key is your identity</p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-white border border-red-100 rounded-lg p-3 text-center">
              <p class="font-bold text-stone-800">Claude OAuth</p>
              <p class="text-stone-500 text-xs mt-1">Sign in with your Spirit Media email &mdash; no API keys</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- First-Time Setup -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="text-2xl">&#x1F5A5;</span>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700">First-Time Setup</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Follow every step in order. Each one builds on the last.</p>

        <div class="space-y-4 mb-6">
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">1.</span>
            <div>Get your <strong>username</strong> from Kevin. Bethel uses <strong>SSH key authentication only</strong> — no passwords.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">2.</span>
            <div>Install <a href="https://tailscale.com/download" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-red-700 hover:underline font-semibold">Tailscale VPN</a>
              <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">Login through Google to <strong>admin@spiritmedia.us</strong>. Notify Kevin for login approval. Bethel is only reachable through Tailscale.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">3.</span>
            <div>Generate an SSH key on your machine:
              <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-3 py-2 mt-1 font-mono text-sm">ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "<span class="text-red-700">yourname</span>@spiritmedia.us"</div>
              <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">Press Enter to accept defaults. Your public key will be saved at <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded">~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub</code></p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">4.</span>
            <div>Copy your public key and send it to Kevin:
              <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-3 py-2 mt-1 font-mono text-sm">cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub</div>
              <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">Send the entire output to Kevin. He will add it to your account on Bethel before you can connect.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">5.</span>
            <div>Add Bethel to your SSH config. Open <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">~/.ssh/config</code> and add:
              <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-3 py-2 mt-1 font-mono text-sm">
                Host bethel<br/>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;HostName 100.114.220.65<br/>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;User <span class="text-red-700">yourusername</span><br/>
                &nbsp;&nbsp;IdentityFile ~/.ssh/id_ed25519
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">6.</span>
            <div>Connect to Bethel:
              <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-3 py-2 mt-1 font-mono text-sm">ssh bethel</div>
              <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">No password prompt — your key authenticates automatically. You should see <em>&ldquo;Spirit Media &mdash; Bethel Server&rdquo;</em>.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">7.</span>
            <div>Run Claude Code for the first time:
              <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-3 py-2 mt-1 font-mono text-sm">claude</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">8.</span>
            <div>
              <p>When asked to choose a login method, select <strong>option 1 — Claude account with subscription</strong> (Pro, Max, Team, or Enterprise).</p>
              <div class="mt-2 p-3 bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded text-sm text-amber-800">
                ⚠️ Do <strong>not</strong> select option 2 (Anthropic Console / API key) or option 3 (third-party platform).
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">9.</span>
            <div>
              <p>A URL will appear in the terminal. <strong>Copy it and open it in a browser on your local machine.</strong></p>
              <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">The browser won&rsquo;t open automatically — you must copy and paste the URL yourself.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">10.</span>
            <div>
              <p>Sign in at <strong>claude.ai</strong> using your <strong>Spirit Media team email</strong> — the one Kevin invited you with (e.g. <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">yourname@spiritmedia.us</code>).</p>
              <div class="mt-2 p-3 bg-stone-50 border border-stone-200 rounded text-sm text-stone-600">
                💡 If your browser is already logged into a personal Claude account, log out first, then sign in with your Spirit Media email.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">11.</span>
            <div><strong>This is a one-time setup.</strong> Claude Code saves your session — future sessions just run <code class="bg-stone-100 px-1 rounded text-xs">claude</code> with no login prompt.</div>
          </div>
        </div>

      </section>

      <!-- Every Session -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="text-2xl">&#x1F504;</span>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700">Every Session</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="text-stone-600 mb-4">Once setup is done, this is your daily workflow. Four steps, every time.</p>

        <div class="mb-4 p-3 bg-red-50 border border-red-200 rounded-lg text-sm text-red-800">
          <strong>Enforced by pre-edit hook.</strong> You must start Claude from inside a specific site directory. Running it from <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded text-xs">~/</code> or <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded text-xs">~/Sites/</code> is blocked &mdash; this prevents Claude from applying the wrong rules to the wrong site.
        </div>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">1.</span>
            <div>Make sure <strong>Tailscale is connected</strong>, then open Terminal and connect:
              <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-3 py-2 mt-1 font-mono text-sm">ssh bethel</div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">2.</span>
            <div>Go to the site you want to work on <strong>and start Claude in one command</strong>:
              <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-3 py-2 mt-1 font-mono text-sm">cd ~/Sites/<span class="text-red-700">site-name</span> && claude</div>
              <p class="text-xs text-stone-500 mt-1">Claude reads the project&rsquo;s CLAUDE.md automatically &mdash; it knows the design system, CMS config, deploy rules, and everything specific to that site.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">3.</span>
            <div>Talk to it in <strong>plain English</strong>:
              <div class="bg-stone-100 rounded px-3 py-2 mt-1 text-sm space-y-1">
                <p class="italic">&ldquo;What other sites are available?&rdquo;</p>
                <p class="italic">&ldquo;Make sure the site builds correctly&rdquo;</p>
                <p class="italic">&ldquo;Fix any broken imports&rdquo;</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-700 font-bold shrink-0">4.</span>
            <div>To exit: <code class="bg-stone-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">/exit</code></div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-6 p-4 bg-pink-50 border border-pink-200 rounded-lg">
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-700"><strong>Parallel sessions:</strong> Open multiple Terminal tabs, SSH into bethel in each, go to a different site, and run <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded text-xs">claude</code>. Each tab is its own independent session.</p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Troubleshooting -->
      <section class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="text-2xl">&#x1F527;</span>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700">Troubleshooting</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-4 text-sm">
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800">&ldquo;Connection refused&rdquo; or can&rsquo;t reach server</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mt-1">Make sure Tailscale VPN is connected. The server is only reachable through VPN.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800">&ldquo;Permission denied (publickey)&rdquo;</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mt-1">Your SSH key hasn&rsquo;t been added to Bethel yet. Send your public key (<code class="bg-white px-1 rounded text-xs">cat ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub</code>) to Kevin and he will add it to your account.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-3 bg-stone-50 rounded-lg">
            <p class="font-semibold text-stone-800">Claude says &ldquo;Max or Pro is required&rdquo; during login</p>
            <p class="text-stone-600 mt-1">You signed in with a personal Claude account that doesn&rsquo;t have a subscription. Log out of claude.ai in your browser, then sign back in with your Spirit Media team email (e.g. <code class="bg-white px-1 rounded text-xs">yourname@spiritmedia.us</code>).</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

    </div>
  </div>
</PortalLayout>
